Our staging deployment for the ContosoPayments service failed at 2:30 AM during the automated release pipeline. The Azure Resource Manager returned a 'ResourceDeploymentFailure' error. I'm pasting the relevant section of our ARM template so you can see the config:

{
  "$schema": "https://schema.management.azure.com/schemas/2019-04-01/deploymentTemplate.json#",
  "contentVersion": "1.0.0.0",
  "parameters": {
    "appServicePlanSku": {
      "type": "string",
      "defaultValue": "P2v3",
      "allowedValues": ["P1v3", "P2v3", "P3v3"]
    },
    "sqlServerAdminPassword": {
      "type": "securestring",
      "metadata": {
        "description": "SQL admin password from Key Vault"
      }
    }
  },
  "resources": [
    {
      "type": "Microsoft.Web/serverfarms",
      "apiVersion": "2022-03-01",
      "name": "asp-contosopay-staging",
      "location": "[resourceGroup().location]",
      "sku": {
        "name": "[parameters('appServicePlanSku')]",
        "capacity": 3
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "Microsoft.Web/sites",
      "apiVersion": "2022-03-01",
      "name": "app-contosopay-staging",
      "location": "[resourceGroup().location]",
      "dependsOn": [
        "[resourceId('Microsoft.Web/serverfarms', 'asp-contosopay-staging')]"
      ],
      "properties": {
        "serverFarmId": "[resourceId('Microsoft.Web/serverfarms', 'asp-contosopay-staging')]",
        "siteConfig": {
          "alwaysOn": true,
          "linuxFxVersion": "DOTNETCORE|8.0",
          "appSettings": [
            {
              "name": "APPINSIGHTS_INSTRUMENTATIONKEY",
              "value": "[reference(resourceId('Microsoft.Insights/components', 'ai-contosopay-staging')).InstrumentationKey]"
            },
            {
              "name": "ConnectionStrings__PaymentDb",
              "value": "[concat('Server=tcp:', reference(resourceId('Microsoft.Sql/servers', 'sql-contosopay-staging')).fullyQualifiedDomainName, ',1433;Database=PaymentDb;')]}"
            }
          ]
        }
      }
    }
  ]
}

The actual error message from the deployment log is:
"Code: ResourceNotFound, Message: The Resource 'Microsoft.Insights/components/ai-contosopay-staging' under resource group 'rg-contosopay-staging' was not found."

It seems like the Application Insights resource doesn't exist yet in staging. We just created this new staging resource group last week and I think we missed adding the App Insights resource to the template.

Can someone help us add the missing resource and re-run the deployment? We need staging up for UAT testing that starts Monday.

James Okoro
DevOps Engineer
Payments Platform Team
Remote — Toronto Office
